    "path": "/Seam-Carving-for-Content-Aware-Image-Resizing/",
    "result": {"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Xiwen's Digital Garden"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"0174c754-49d8-5774-8323-b6e6fd2ae3ab","excerpt":"Authors: Shai Avidan, Ariel Shamir Published In: SIGGRAPH ‘07: ACM SIGGRAPH 2007 DOI/ISBN: 10.1145/1275808.1276390 1. Abstract What do we already know…","html":"<p><strong>Authors</strong>: Shai Avidan, Ariel Shamir</p>\n<p><strong>Published In</strong>: SIGGRAPH ‘07: ACM SIGGRAPH 2007</p>\n<p><strong>DOI/ISBN</strong>: 10.1145/1275808.1276390</p>\n<h2>1. Abstract</h2>\n<h3>What do we already know?</h3>\n<p>Traditional image resizing and cropping to support HTML page layouts on multiple screen dimensions.</p>\n<h3>What do we want to solve?</h3>\n<p>Resizing images without distorting the structure and content of the image.</p>\n<h3>How did the author(s) solve that problem?</h3>\n<p>The authors introduce seam-carving: find paths of minimum ‘importance’ (seams) from top to bottom or left to right of an image, and removes seams to reduce image size or insert seams to extend the image. The ‘importance’ of pixels in paths is defined using an energy function, which allows the algorithm to preserve important details/contents in an image.</p>\n<h3>What did the author(s) find?</h3>\n<p>A new algorithm to dynamically resize image by artificially inserting and removing low energy pixels. Usage:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Content-aware resizing (e.g. in Adobe Photoshop)</li>\n<li>Remove objects from images</li>\n<li>Image retargeting, dynamically resize images for optimal display on different resolutions. However, the produced output is objectively worse compared to many other algorithms <a href=\"http://people.csail.mit.edu/mrub/papers/retBenchmark.pdf\">(source)</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h2>2. Contents</h2>\n<h3>Step 1: Calculate the energy of each pixel</h3>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 400px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/ee2d01ccd81030d40c033ee4fbc9a05b/066f9/ip1_1_initial.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 67.08860759493672%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Initial image\"\n        title=\"Initial image\"\n        src=\"/static/ee2d01ccd81030d40c033ee4fbc9a05b/066f9/ip1_1_initial.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/ee2d01ccd81030d40c033ee4fbc9a05b/ff44c/ip1_1_initial.jpg 158w,\n/static/ee2d01ccd81030d40c033ee4fbc9a05b/a6688/ip1_1_initial.jpg 315w,\n/static/ee2d01ccd81030d40c033ee4fbc9a05b/066f9/ip1_1_initial.jpg 400w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 400px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/2abfd5ba7ac9e53ac4710f7a4a5b89f3/066f9/ip1_2_gradient.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 67.08860759493672%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Gradient magnitude of an image\"\n        title=\"Gradient magnitude of an image\"\n        src=\"/static/2abfd5ba7ac9e53ac4710f7a4a5b89f3/066f9/ip1_2_gradient.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/2abfd5ba7ac9e53ac4710f7a4a5b89f3/ff44c/ip1_2_gradient.jpg 158w,\n/static/2abfd5ba7ac9e53ac4710f7a4a5b89f3/a6688/ip1_2_gradient.jpg 315w,\n/static/2abfd5ba7ac9e53ac4710f7a4a5b89f3/066f9/ip1_2_gradient.jpg 400w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>Energy can be calculated using image gradient magnitude, entropy, visual saliency, eye-gaze movement etc. For simplicity, we use <a href=\"notes/edge_detection/#image-gradient\">gradient magnitude</a>. In this case, we define the energy function as follow:</p>\n<div class=\"math math-display\"><span class=\"katex-display\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" display=\"block\"><semantics><mrow><mi>G</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi mathvariant=\"bold\">I</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo>=</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">∣</mi><mfrac><mi>δ</mi><mrow><mi>δ</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"bold\">I</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">∣</mi><mo>+</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">∣</mi><mfrac><mi>δ</mi><mrow><mi>δ</mi><mi>y</mi></mrow></mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"bold\">I</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">∣</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">G(\\mathbf{I})=|\\frac{\\delta}{\\delta x}\\mathbf{I}|+|\\frac{\\delta}{\\delta y}\\mathbf{I}|</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">G</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathbf\">I</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:2.0574em;vertical-align:-0.686em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">∣</span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mopen nulldelimiter\"></span><span class=\"mfrac\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:1.3714em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.314em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.03785em;\">δ</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">x</span></span></span><span style=\"top:-3.23em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"frac-line\" style=\"border-bottom-width:0.04em;\"></span></span><span style=\"top:-3.677em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.03785em;\">δ</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.686em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mclose nulldelimiter\"></span></span><span class=\"mord mathbf\">I</span><span class=\"mord\">∣</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">+</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:2.2519em;vertical-align:-0.8804em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">∣</span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mopen nulldelimiter\"></span><span class=\"mfrac\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:1.3714em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.314em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.03588em;\">δy</span></span></span><span style=\"top:-3.23em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"frac-line\" style=\"border-bottom-width:0.04em;\"></span></span><span style=\"top:-3.677em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.03785em;\">δ</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.8804em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mclose nulldelimiter\"></span></span><span class=\"mord mathbf\">I</span><span class=\"mord\">∣</span></span></span></span></span></div>\n<p>where <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"bold\">I</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\mathbf{I}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6861em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathbf\">I</span></span></span></span></span> is the 2D input matrix of an image.</p>\n<h3>Step 2: Find a list of seams</h3>\n<p>Next, we want to find seams by ascending order of energy.</p>\n<p><strong>What are seams?</strong></p>\n<p>A seam <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"bold\">s</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\mathbf{s}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.4444em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathbf\">s</span></span></span></span></span> is an <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pixel_connectivity#8-connected\">8-connected</a> path of pixels with minimum energy. It goes from top to bottom (vertical seam) or left to right (horizontal seam) in an image.</p>\n<div class=\"math math-display\"><span class=\"katex-display\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" display=\"block\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"bold\">s</mi><mo>=</mo><mo stretchy=\"false\">{</mo><msub><mi>s</mi><mi>i</mi></msub><msubsup><mo stretchy=\"false\">}</mo><mrow><mi>i</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mi>n</mi></msubsup><mo>=</mo><mo stretchy=\"false\">{</mo><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>i</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo><mi>y</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>i</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo stretchy=\"false\">}</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">_</mi><msup><mrow><mi>i</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mi>n</mi></msup></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\mathbf{s}=\\{s_i\\}_{i=1}^n = \\{(x(i),y(i))\\}\\_{i=1}^n</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.4444em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathbf\">s</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mopen\">{</span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">s</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.3117em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.55em;margin-left:0em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">i</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mclose\"><span class=\"mclose\">}</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.7144em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.453em;margin-left:0em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">i</span><span class=\"mrel mtight\">=</span><span class=\"mord mtight\">1</span></span></span></span><span style=\"top:-3.113em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">n</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.247em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1.06em;vertical-align:-0.31em;\"></span><span class=\"mopen\">{(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">x</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">i</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.03588em;\">y</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">i</span><span class=\"mclose\">))}</span><span class=\"mord\" style=\"margin-right:0.02778em;\">_</span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">i</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">1</span></span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.7144em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.113em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">n</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></div>\n<p><span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"bold\">I</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><msub><mi>s</mi><mi>i</mi></msub><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\mathbf{I}(s_i)</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathbf\">I</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">s</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.3117em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.55em;margin-left:0em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">i</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span></span> will then be the <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>i</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">i</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6595em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">i</span></span></span></span></span>-th pixel on the path of a seam in image <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"bold\">I</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\mathbf{I}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6861em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathbf\">I</span></span></span></span></span>.</p>\n<p>In a vertical seam, each row has one and only one pixel <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>y</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>i</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo>=</mo><mi>i</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">(y(i)=i)</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.03588em;\">y</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">i</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">i</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span></span>; In a horizontal seam, each column has one and only one pixel <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>i</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo>=</mo><mi>i</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">(x(i)=i)</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">x</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">i</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">i</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span></span>.</p>\n<p><strong>Why use seams?</strong></p>\n<p>Seams preserve both the rectangular shape and visual coherence of an image.</p>\n<p><strong>Objective</strong></p>\n<p>Let <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>E</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi mathvariant=\"bold\">s</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">E(\\mathbf{s})</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.05764em;\">E</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathbf\">s</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span></span> be the total energy cost of a seam, we want to find an optimal seam <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msup><mi mathvariant=\"bold\">s</mi><mo>∗</mo></msup></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\mathbf{s}^*</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6887em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathbf\">s</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.6887em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.063em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mbin mtight\">∗</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> that minimizes total cost:</p>\n<div class=\"math math-display\"><span class=\"katex-display\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" display=\"block\"><semantics><mrow><msup><mi mathvariant=\"bold\">s</mi><mo>∗</mo></msup><mo>=</mo><msub><mtext>argmin</mtext><mi mathvariant=\"bold\">s</mi></msub><mi>E</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi mathvariant=\"bold\">s</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo>=</mo><msub><mtext>argmin</mtext><mi mathvariant=\"bold\">s</mi></msub><munderover><mo>∑</mo><mrow><mi>i</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mi>n</mi></munderover><mi>G</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi mathvariant=\"bold\">I</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><msub><mi>s</mi><mi>i</mi></msub><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\mathbf{s}^* =\\text{argmin}_\\mathbf{s}E(\\mathbf{\\mathbf{s}})=\\text{argmin}_\\mathbf{s}\\sum_{i=1}^n G(\\mathbf{I}(s_i))</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.7387em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathbf\">s</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.7387em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.113em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mbin mtight\">∗</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord text\"><span class=\"mord\">argmin</span></span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.067em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.4559em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathbf mtight\">s</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.2441em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.05764em;\">E</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathbf\">s</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:2.9291em;vertical-align:-1.2777em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord text\"><span class=\"mord\">argmin</span></span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.067em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.4559em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathbf mtight\">s</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.2441em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mop op-limits\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:1.6514em;\"><span style=\"top:-1.8723em;margin-left:0em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3.05em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">i</span><span class=\"mrel mtight\">=</span><span class=\"mord mtight\">1</span></span></span></span><span style=\"top:-3.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3.05em;\"></span><span><span class=\"mop op-symbol large-op\">∑</span></span></span><span style=\"top:-4.3em;margin-left:0em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3.05em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">n</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:1.2777em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">G</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathbf\">I</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">s</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.3117em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.55em;margin-left:0em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">i</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mclose\">))</span></span></span></span></span></div>\n<p>In practice, this can be done via Dijkstra’s algorithm, dynamic programming, greedy algorithm, graph cuts etc. Here is a dynamic programming example for vertical seams:</p>\n<div class=\"math math-display\"><span class=\"katex-display\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" display=\"block\"><semantics><mrow><mi>M</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>i</mi><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo><mi>j</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo>=</mo><mi>G</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>i</mi><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo><mi>j</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo>+</mo><mi>min</mi><mo>⁡</mo><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>M</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>i</mi><mo>−</mo><mn>1</mn><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo><mi>j</mi><mo>−</mo><mn>1</mn><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo><mi>M</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>i</mi><mo>−</mo><mn>1</mn><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo><mi>j</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo><mi>M</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>i</mi><mo>−</mo><mn>1</mn><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo><mi>j</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">M(i,j)=G(i,j)+\\min(M(i-1,j-1),M(i-1,j),M(i-1,j+1))</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.10903em;\">M</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">i</span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.05724em;\">j</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">G</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">i</span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.05724em;\">j</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">+</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mop\">min</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.10903em;\">M</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">i</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">−</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.854em;vertical-align:-0.1944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">1</span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.05724em;\">j</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">−</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">1</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.10903em;\">M</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">i</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">−</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">1</span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.05724em;\">j</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.10903em;\">M</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">i</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">−</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.854em;vertical-align:-0.1944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">1</span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.05724em;\">j</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">+</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">1</span><span class=\"mclose\">))</span></span></span></span></span></div>\n<p>where <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>M</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">M</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.10903em;\">M</span></span></span></span></span> is the cumulative minimum energy for all possible connected seams for each pixel <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>i</mi><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo><mi>j</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">(i,j)</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">i</span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.05724em;\">j</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span></span>. Then, we <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Backtracking\">backtrack</a> from min value in last row of <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>M</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">M</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.10903em;\">M</span></span></span></span></span> to get an optimal seam path.</p>\n<p><figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 399px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/e6a0b9b6e3da9d8ae5a45973abc5e846/01983/ip1_3_dp.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 67.08860759493672%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Dynamic programming result\"\n        title=\"Dynamic programming result $M$ on the image gradient magnitude\"\n        src=\"/static/e6a0b9b6e3da9d8ae5a45973abc5e846/01983/ip1_3_dp.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/e6a0b9b6e3da9d8ae5a45973abc5e846/ff44c/ip1_3_dp.jpg 158w,\n/static/e6a0b9b6e3da9d8ae5a45973abc5e846/a6688/ip1_3_dp.jpg 315w,\n/static/e6a0b9b6e3da9d8ae5a45973abc5e846/01983/ip1_3_dp.jpg 399w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 399px) 100vw, 399px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span>\n    <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\"><p>Dynamic programming result <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>M</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">M</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.10903em;\">M</span></span></span></span></span> on the image gradient magnitude</p></figcaption>\n  </figure></p>\n<p><figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 399px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/f417828c427b752158bc18d4415b1705/01983/ip1_4_seam1.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 67.08860759493672%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Vertical seam in an image\"\n        title=\"Backtracking to obtain optimal seam (1/2)\"\n        src=\"/static/f417828c427b752158bc18d4415b1705/01983/ip1_4_seam1.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/f417828c427b752158bc18d4415b1705/ff44c/ip1_4_seam1.jpg 158w,\n/static/f417828c427b752158bc18d4415b1705/a6688/ip1_4_seam1.jpg 315w,\n/static/f417828c427b752158bc18d4415b1705/01983/ip1_4_seam1.jpg 399w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 399px) 100vw, 399px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span>\n    <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\"><p>Backtracking to obtain optimal seam (1/2)</p></figcaption>\n  </figure></p>\n<p><figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 399px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/ddc9bb93c37de90503b25bf7f07896d7/01983/ip1_5_seam2.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 67.08860759493672%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Vertical seam in an image\"\n        title=\"Backtracking to obtain optimal seam (2/2)\"\n        src=\"/static/ddc9bb93c37de90503b25bf7f07896d7/01983/ip1_5_seam2.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/ddc9bb93c37de90503b25bf7f07896d7/ff44c/ip1_5_seam2.jpg 158w,\n/static/ddc9bb93c37de90503b25bf7f07896d7/a6688/ip1_5_seam2.jpg 315w,\n/static/ddc9bb93c37de90503b25bf7f07896d7/01983/ip1_5_seam2.jpg 399w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 399px) 100vw, 399px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span>\n    <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\"><p>Backtracking to obtain optimal seam (2/2)</p></figcaption>\n  </figure></p>\n<h3>Step 3: Do something to the seams</h3>\n<p>To crop the image, remove seams in ascending order of energy as needed; To extend the image, duplicate seams as needed.</p>\n<p><figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 500px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/895f657d3d51c75cdf7622c11edae3ce/41099/ip1_6_larger.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 53.79746835443038%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Enlarged image\"\n        title=\"Extend the image vertically by 100 pixels, using seam carving. Observe that the waves are not distorted, compared to conventional scaling methods.\"\n        src=\"/static/895f657d3d51c75cdf7622c11edae3ce/41099/ip1_6_larger.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/895f657d3d51c75cdf7622c11edae3ce/ff44c/ip1_6_larger.jpg 158w,\n/static/895f657d3d51c75cdf7622c11edae3ce/a6688/ip1_6_larger.jpg 315w,\n/static/895f657d3d51c75cdf7622c11edae3ce/41099/ip1_6_larger.jpg 500w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span>\n    <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\"><p>Extend the image vertically by 100 pixels, using seam carving. Observe that the waves are not distorted, compared to conventional scaling methods.</p></figcaption>\n  </figure></p>\n<h2>3. Conclusion</h2>\n<h3>Limitations</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>May require additional data to reduce errors. For example, images with human faces may require face detectors.</li>\n<li>If the image is too condensed where every part appears to be equally important, or if an important region is laid out in a way that blocks seams from bypassing, it will be less performant.</li>\n<li>In some cases, removing a low-energy seam may create a new seam of higher energy. A solution to this is forward energy enhancement. When calculating <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>M</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">M</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.10903em;\">M</span></span></span></span></span>, the algorithm accounts for changes in energy from new neighbors if a seam is hypothetically removed.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Resources</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Original <a href=\"https://www.win.tue.nl/~wstahw/edu/2IV05/seamcarving.pdf\">paper</a> by Avidan, Shai &#x26; Shamir, Ariel. (2007). Seam Carving for Content-Aware Image Resizing. SIGGRAPH. 26. 10.1145/1276377.1276390.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=vIFCV2spKtg\">Video</a> demonstration on Youtube</li>\n<li>This <a href=\"https://www.aryan.app/seam-carving/\">website</a> allows you to upload an image and see how it works</li>\n<li>Many <a href=\"http://cs.brown.edu/courses/cs129/results/proj3/taox/\">examples</a> of resized images</li>\n<li>Images generated using a <a href=\"https://www.mathworks.com/matlabcentral/fileexchange/18089-seam-carving-for-content-aware-image-resizing-gui-implementation-demo\">GUI implementation demo</a> by Danny Luong (2021).</li>\n</ul>","frontmatter":{"title":"Seam Carving for Content-Aware Image Resizing","date":"August 30, 2021","description":"The authors resize images by inserting or deleting low energy horizontal/vertical seams. This preserves the features and the content of the image."}},"previous":null,"next":{"fields":{"slug":"/Face-Spoofing-2D-Detection-Based-on-Moiré-Pattern-Analysis/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Face-Spoofing 2D-Detection Based on Moiré Pattern Analysis"}}},"pageContext":{"id":"0174c754-49d8-5774-8323-b6e6fd2ae3ab","previousPostId":null,"nextPostId":"69e7100e-7b2e-56f8-b904-0080c6668055"}},
